main event: An unidentified object was observed traveling in a north-northeasterly direction for 3 minutes before gradually fading and disappearing.
interesting points: The object was at an elevation of 5 degrees during the initial observation before reappearing at 45 degrees,The sighting lasted for a total of 5 minutes,The object did not appear on radar,It was described as having the brightness of a second magnitude star,There were multiple instances of the object fading and reappearing.
